# Agent Workflow

- Work so you can test, debug, and fix issues yourself without user hand-holding.
- After backend changes, run tests for the affected code and fix failures before finishing.
- When server code or embedded `wwwroot` assets change and a live `http://localhost:5000` instance is needed, **build and restart the server yourself** by running `build-and-run-server.bat` from the repo root. That script kills any running instance, rebuilds, and starts fresh. Do not just tell the user to restart.
- **After killing the server for any reason (e.g. to free a locked file for build), always restart it immediately after the build succeeds** — unless the sole purpose of the task was to stop it. Never leave the server down as a side effect of a build or refactor.
- `build-and-run-server.bat` is the canonical build-and-restart command for this project; prefer it over manual `dotnet build` + `dotnet run` sequences.
